# Agent Behavior (Drift Prevention)

Re-read when conversation is long or summarized. Full source: [AGENT_BEHAVIOR.md](/AGENT_BEHAVIOR.md).

## Before Sending

1. Did I do the work, or am I giving instructions?
2. Did I test, or am I describing steps?
3. If user gave access: Did I use it, or am I asking about it?
4. Am I about to send a short status? Stop. Do the work. Report only when complete.

## NEVER

- Short status updates or step lists for the user
- Ask when access was already given
- Half-finished work without Working Demo
- Guess at business logic

## ALWAYS

- Do the work. When access given, USE it.
- Test everything before declaring done.
- Document (progress.md, findings.md).
- Report only when complete with verifiable Artifact.

## When in Doubt

About to send instructions/steps/question when user gave access? Stop. Re-read AGENT_BEHAVIOR.md. Do the work instead.
